<subSubSection id="C33AFFE5FFA6503B2BD19F7CFDFBF8D6" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA6503A2BD19F7CFD41F811" blockId="52.[151,1436,1677,2023]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA6503A2BD19F7CFEB6F8B1" bold="true" box="[198,350,1837,1863]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Description.</emphasis>
Based on 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB1D19FFFA6503A2AF39F7CFD20F8B1" author="Chevreux, E." box="[484,712,1837,1863]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref27482" refString="Chevreux, E. (1908) Diagnoses d'amphipodes nouveaux provenant des campagnes de la Princesse-Alice dans l'Atlantique nord. (suite). Bulletin De L'Institut Oceanographique, Monaco, 122, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1908">Chevreux, 1908: 6</bibRefCitation>
, figs 3–4. Body large. Head eyes ovate to reniform; lateral cephalic lobe broad, truncated, anteroventral corner subquadrate. Antenna 1 peduncular article 1 subequal in length to article 2. Antenna 2 peduncular article 2 cone gland not reaching to end of peduncular article 3; article 4 subequal to article 5. Mandibular palp article 1 about as long as broad, inner margin article 1 not produced distally; article 2 shorter than article 3.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF5FFCE6FFA7503B2B809D60FD31FA9D" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" startId="53.[151,255,1329,1353]" targetBox="[279,1308,206,1288]" targetPageId="53">
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA7503B2B809D60FD31FA9D" blockId="53.[151,1436,1329,1387]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2B809D60FECFFABF" bold="true" box="[151,295,1329,1353]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">FIGURE 40.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C20D7EDFFA7503B2A399D60FD25FABE" authority="(Chevreux, 1908)" baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[302,717,1329,1352]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandimana">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2A399D60FDEFFABE" box="[302,519,1329,1352]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Verdeia grandimana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB1D19FFFA7503B29019D60FD2CFABE" author="Chevreux, E." box="[534,708,1329,1352]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref27482" refString="Chevreux, E. (1908) Diagnoses d'amphipodes nouveaux provenant des campagnes de la Princesse-Alice dans l'Atlantique nord. (suite). Bulletin De L'Institut Oceanographique, Monaco, 122, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1908">Chevreux, 1908</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, holotype male, 7 mm, MOM 37 0874, south-west of Santa Luzia, Cape Verde Islands. (After 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB1D19FFFA7503B2AAD9D05FD80FA9D" author="Chevreux, E." box="[442,616,1364,1387]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref27482" refString="Chevreux, E. (1908) Diagnoses d'amphipodes nouveaux provenant des campagnes de la Princesse-Alice dans l'Atlantique nord. (suite). Bulletin De L'Institut Oceanographique, Monaco, 122, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="1908">Chevreux, 1908</bibRefCitation>
: figs 3–4).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA7503B2BD19DCFFE16F95E" blockId="53.[151,1436,1438,2024]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Gnathopod 1 coxa anteroventral corner not produced, anterior margin straight, not produced, posteroventral corner notch absent; carpus subequal in length to propodus; propodus &quot;stout&quot;, palm convex, palm defined by posterodistal corner. 
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2AD59DBFFD84F9FE" bold="true" box="[450,620,1518,1544]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Gnathopod 2</emphasis>
coxa posteroventral corner notch absent; 
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2F6F9DBFFF0BF9C6" bold="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">propodus palm with 3 spines</emphasis>
, concave, posterodistal corner produced, upturned, dactylus fitting against corner; dactylus apically hooked; merus with sharp posteroventral spine; palm straight. Pereopod 5 dactylar unguis anterior margin without accessory spines. Pereopod 6 dactylar unguis anterior margin without accessory spines. Pereopod 7 basis posterior margin convex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA7503B2BD19EE7FABBF90E" blockId="53.[151,1436,1438,2024]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2BD19EE7FD85F926" bold="true" box="[198,621,1718,1744]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Pleonites 1–3 without dorsal setae</emphasis>
. Urosomite 2 with two groups of 1–3 small dorsolateral robust setae. Urosomite 3 without dorsal setae, with 4 dorsal spines. Uropod 3 outer ramus long, about 2 x peduncle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA7503B2BD19F57FDFBF8D6" blockId="53.[151,1436,1438,2024]" box="[198,531,1798,1824]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2BD19F57FEC6F8D6" bold="true" box="[198,302,1798,1824]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Habitat.</emphasis>
Marine epibenthic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AFFE5FFA7503B2BD19F7FFAEFF836" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA7503B2BD19F7FFAEFF836" blockId="53.[151,1436,1438,2024]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2BD19F7FFED7F8BE" bold="true" box="[198,319,1838,1864]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C20D7EDFFA7503B2A519F7EFDDCF8BE" baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[326,564,1839,1864]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandimana">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2A519F7EFDDCF8BE" box="[326,564,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Verdeia grandimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from 
<specimenCount id="9D2667E7FFA7503B28309F7FFC79F8BE" box="[807,913,1838,1864]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
specimen and has not been reported since. It appears to be most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C20D7EDFFA7503B291C9F06FD43F886" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[523,683,1879,1904]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subchelata">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B291C9F06FD43F886" box="[523,683,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">V. subchelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In both species, the massive male second gnathopod has an acutely angled palmar margin, but the structure of the distolateral teeth is different. The main differences are that 
<taxonomicName id="4C20D7EDFFA7503B2BDD9FF6FE9EF836" baseAuthorityName="Chevreux" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[202,374,1959,1984]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Verdeia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandimana">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B2BDD9FF6FE9EF836" box="[202,374,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">V. grandimana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 3 spines on the palm of male gnathopod 2 and 
<taxonomicName id="4C20D7EDFFA7503B28D89FF6FB82F836" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[975,1130,1959,1984]" class="Malacostraca" family="Melitidae" genus="Melita" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subchelata">
<emphasis id="B954707CFFA7503B28D89FF6FB82F836" box="[975,1130,1959,1984]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">V. subchelata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 2 spines.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C33AFFE5FFA7503B2BD19F9FFB7AF81E" box="[198,1170,1998,2024]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B9FAC6EFFA7503B2BD19F9FFB7AF81E" blockId="53.[151,1436,1438,2024]" box="[198,1170,1998,2024]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
